Package core

Interface HlaPhysicalEntityManagerListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HlaPhysicalEntityManagerListener.Adapter
    public interface HlaPhysicalEntityManagerListener
    Listener for changes of HlaPhysicalEntity instances.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      static class  HlaPhysicalEntityManagerListener.Adapter
      An abstract adapter class that implements the HlaPhysicalEntityManagerListener interface with empty methods.

    • Method Detail

      • hlaPhysicalEntityDiscovered

        void hlaPhysicalEntityDiscovered​(HlaPhysicalEntity physicalEntity,
                                 HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a new HlaPhysicalEntity instance is discovered. A discovered instance is initially within interest.
        Parameters:
        physicalEntity - the object which is discovered
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaPhysicalEntityInitialized

        void hlaPhysicalEntityInitialized​(HlaPhysicalEntity physicalEntity,
                                  HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                                  HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaPhysicalEntity instance is initialized. An instance is initialized when it has been discovered and all attribute marked with initialized has a value.
        Parameters:
        physicalEntity - the object which is initialized
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated

      • hlaPhysicalEntityInInterest

        void hlaPhysicalEntityInInterest​(HlaPhysicalEntity physicalEntity,
                                 HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaPhysicalEntity instance comes within interest. A discovered instance is initially within interest, so this will not be called at the time of discovery.
        Parameters:
        physicalEntity - the object which has come into interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaPhysicalEntityOutOfInterest

        void hlaPhysicalEntityOutOfInterest​(HlaPhysicalEntity physicalEntity,
                                    HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaPhysicalEntity instance goes out of interest.
        Parameters:
        physicalEntity - the object which has gone out of interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaPhysicalEntityDeleted

        void hlaPhysicalEntityDeleted​(HlaPhysicalEntity physicalEntity,
                              HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                              HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaPhysicalEntity instance is deleted.
        Parameters:
        physicalEntity - the object which is deleted
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated
